HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1104
By Pearson
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Hamilton Middle
School Wildcats boys' basketball team upon
winning the 2026 Memphis Shelby County
Interscholastic Athletic Association Class A
Championship.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize
those outstanding young people who, through their athletic endeavors, have distinguished
themselves and brought honor to their school and community; and
WHEREAS, the Hamilton Middle School Wildcats boys' basketball team demonstrated
remarkable skill, determination, and teamwork throughout the 2025-2026 season, which
culminated in an impressive victory to capture the 2026 Memphis Shelby County Interscholastic
Athletic Association Class A Championship; and
WHEREAS, the Wildcats exhibited extraordinary discipline, sportsmanship, and unity on
the court, embodying the highest ideals of athletic competition and representing Hamilton
Middle School with pride and excellence; and
WHEREAS, the championship victory stands as a testament to the hard work and
dedication of the student athletes, the leadership and guidance of their coaches, and the
unwavering support of their families, teachers, and the entire Hamilton Middle School
community; and
WHEREAS, during the championship game, Jeremiah S. delivered an exceptional
performance and was deservedly named the Most Valuable Player for his demonstration of
leadership, determination, and outstanding athletic ability; and
WHEREAS, the Hamilton Middle School Wildcats have brought great pride to their
school and the Memphis community, serving as an inspiration to their fellow students and
aspiring young athletes alike; now, therefore,
HJR1104
015269
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the Hamilton Middle School Wildcats boys'
basketball team upon winning the 2026 Memphis Shelby County Interscholastic Athletic
Association Class A Championship and commend the players, coaches, and supporters for their
dedication, teamwork, and outstanding achievement.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
